      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-01486'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040511_GCR_75' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 12 [<span class="italic">Other services</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-01487'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040511_GCR_76' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Baroness Hanham</span> moved Amendment No. 12:
        <q>Page 7, line 28, at end insert "so long as such provision does not impair the authority's discharge of the functions conferred on it by sections 6, 7, 8 and 9</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-01488'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040511_GCR_77' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Baroness said: Clause 12 provides fire and rescue authorities with the power to provide the services of their employees and equipment for any purpose they consider appropriate inside or outside their area. It refers also to commercial services which might be provided by the authority. It is useful to have those resources available for the benefit of the community. We have no difficulty with any of that or with the proposals. The services are being provided to individuals in the authority and it is therefore acting no differently from any other service provider.
