      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0661P0-01632'>
        <a name='S5LV0661P0_20040511_GCR_221'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-jeff-rooker' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040511_GCR_221' title='Link to this speech by Mr Jeff Rooker' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-jeff-rooker" title="Mr Jeff Rooker">Lord Rooker</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I shall speak to the group that is being joined together as we speak: Amendments Nos. 64, 65, 66, and I think 66A and 67. I will start with Amendment No. 65. I know that the noble Baroness, Lady Hamwee, is a lawyer, or one of the lawyers that does not count&#x2014;I think that she is a solicitor. I say to her that this issue about the legality of charging&#x2014;I am advised as a pure layman&#x2014;is nowhere near as clear cut as some people make out according to advice within Government. I shall come to that.</p><p>
            I teased the noble Lord, but I pay tribute to the Essex fire authority. I really am sucking up to Essex today. Given what the noble Lord has said that it is doing, it all seemed admirable. I could not see&#x2014;as a lay person&#x2014;anything wrong with what it is doing. It is using its capacity to do good things.
          </p>
